args: That should do it! I think I completed the\nAround the World Kendama Challenge!
Ya got the ball on all the cups and the\nspike, so that's a big ol' win far as I'm\nconcerned. Congrats, Cleo!
Huzzah! Now to move three squares.
We're close as heck now! I know one of us\nis gonna reach the end here soon!
Yeah, we only have about ten spaces to go\nuntil the end. But before that...
It sounds like the last trial is waiting,\nso let's get going!
We managed to make it this far, but...

Those zombies are blocking our path!
And though I know they aren't real,
there are still enough of them to send
chills up my spine.
Don't help that I can't make heads\nor tails of this challenge.
＂Protect the most important thing＂?\nI fear I also do not understand this.\nWhat exactly are we to be protecting?
Is this another one of those Hinomotoan\nriddles? 'Cause if so, we might not wanna\nbe randomly attacking any zombies.
That's certainly possible. Best to figure out\nthe puzzle before we try anything.
But with instructions so vague,\nhow are we meant to solve it?
Don't worry, dudes. I've got this.
Mmm-hmm! Knowing what the creators of\nthis sugoroku wanted their players to\nexperience, I'm certain I have the answer.
The most important thing to me is making\nlots of happy memories with all of you—\nand I won't EVER question that again.
But if I'm gonna protect that, I've gotta\ntake out any obstacles that stand in the\nway of making more memories!
So watch out, zombies, 'cause you're\nall in for a major butt-kicking!
Holy cripes! Notte just charged into that\nhorde'a zombies all by herself!
She normally would have been terrified...
She's like a new person. Something must\nhave happened when we were separated.
And if that's the case, I want to believe\nin the answer she's found.
Pretty sure all of us feel the same, so we\nbetter hustle if we don't wanna miss out!
Hey! Save a zombie for me, lady!
After all, it's much more enjoyable to\nmake memories together than to do so\nby yourself. Right, Notte?
Aw, thanks, guys! \nWith all of us, this'll be done in no time!
GET AWAY FROM MY FRIEND, JERK!\nI'M GONNA PROTECT 'EM ALL!
We did it! We defeated the zombies!\nIs the challenge complete now?
Well, the ground just lit up and there's a\nChallenge Complete stamp on it, sooo...
Sure as shootin', pards! Y'all just beat the\nlast challenge, and it's a straight shot to\nthe finish line!
BLARGH! Ow, ow, ow... Oh, hey!\nI think we're home.
It feels like it's been ages since we last\nset foot in the Halidom.
That sugoroku was fun, but it also kinda\nmessed me up in a whole lot of ways.\nI'm gonna go sleep for a year. Peace.

Do not even think about it, Luca!
I understand you must be worn out,
but I will not have you sleeping on
our freshly cleaned floor.
Well, I'm just pleased as all get-out that\ny'all made it back in one piece.
I'm real shamed to have put ya in such\na sorry situation, but at least it's over.
I also apologize for my fool of a shikigami\nhaving put you through such an ordeal.
So then? What did you think of the\nreal-life sugoroku?
Augh! I can't take the suspense!

IT WAS SOOO HARD!
It's definitely the most exciting thing we've
done for New Year's, and I'm super-duper
glad we tried it.
But that being said, maybe it'd be better\nif New Year's is a more peaceful\ncelebration after all...
New Year's celebrations ARE meant\nto be a time where one prays for a\npeaceful year, I suppose.
But if you want to know if I had fun or not,\nthe answer is yes!
So much happened, and I made all kinds\nof memories that I'll never forget!
Well, I'm happier'n a pig in the sun to\nhear that. If ya ask me, the more happy\nmemories ya make, the better!
And it was your game that helped me\nrealize that, so I guess we BOTH win!
Aw, shucks. It ain't no big deal.
I didn't really do much. But if you truly\nmean all that, you'd better get on and\nenjoy the rest of your New Year's party.
I'm sure you have many more New Year's\nmemories to make, after all.
Oh yeah! I'm gonna make so many that\nthey start spillin' out my ears!
And if you guys are here with us, we'll be\nable to enjoy the holiday even more!
Y'all can count on me, 'cause I got a\nheap'a fun spells ready for this shindig!
Uh...are you sure about that? I mean,\nthe last spell sorta became A Thing, yeah?
Oh, I'm not about to let that happen again;\nI did a thorough check of everything else\nwhile you were off in the game world.
Well, if Seimei says it's safe, then...\nHEY, GUYS!
We've got more New Year's festivities with\nSeimei's seal of approval, so let's try 'em\nout after we finish eating!
I'm up for it! New Year's has only just\nbegun, after all.
Eeexactly! I'm gonna do all kinds of new\nand exciting stuff with you this year—and\nthat's a promise, {player_name}!
